# Copy to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) for `pnpm dev` to read locally
# (`@cloudflare/vite-plugin` loads it into the in-process Worker).
# In production, set each value via:
#
#     wrangler secret put <NAME>
#
# The Worker's `src/server/index.ts` chooses which verifier to use
# based on which of these is set; pick one branch per environment.

# --- Dev-fast-path: shared secret (single-tenant) ---------------
# `dev-shared-secret` matches the client-side fallback in
# `src/web/client.ts`, so `cp .dev.vars.example .dev.vars && pnpm dev`
# works out of the box. For any environment reachable from the
# public internet, replace with a strong random value (e.g.
# `openssl rand -hex 32`) and set the matching `VITE_SHARED_SECRET`
# at build time so the SPA bundle ships the same token.
SHARED_SECRET=dev-shared-secret

# --- Production: Cloudflare Access JWT --------------------------
# Switch `src/server/index.ts` to `cloudflareAccess({ team, audience })`
# (see the `baerly-storage/auth` JSDoc) and uncomment these.
# `team` is the slug part of `<team>.cloudflareaccess.com`;
# `audience` is the Access App's "Audience (AUD) Tag".
# CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=
# CF_ACCESS_AUDIENCE_TAG=
